Structure of C Program : 
------------------------

#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
void main(){
    clrscr();
    printf("Hello world");  
    getch();
}

or

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    printf("Hello world");  
    return 0;
}

--------------------------------------------------

step 1 : Documentation part 
         // Program to print Hello World
         // Hello world program 
         // program to print Hello World

         Single line comment 
         //

         multiple line comment
         /*
              .....
              .....
         */

step 2 : Header Files 
       #include<stdio.h> 
       #include<conio.h>
       #include<stdlib.h>
       #include<math.h>
       #include<string.h> etc 

       #include<stdio.h>
       
       # = preprocessor symbol or preprocessor operator 
       include = file inclusion directive 
       #include = preprocessor directive

       Preprocessor : Preprocessor simply gives instructions to the compiler to pre process the information before actual compilation starts. 

       <> = tags

       stdio.h = standard input output . h
                 here .h is the extension of header file
       conio.h = console input output .h 
       stdlib.h = standard library .h

step 3 : int main() | void main() | _____ main()
                                     int 

      here int , void are the return types
      where int returns integer value
      and void represents that the specific function does not return any value.

step 4 : {    represents opening of main function definition part 
step 5 : clrscr(); performs cleaning action (clears the output terminal)
step 6 : printf(); performs printing operation
                   here f represents formatted function, which means it can contains format specifier.
step 7 : getch(); | return 0; 
         here getch() means get a character
         getch() simply holds the output screen 
         getche() it represents by which character we terminate output screen

         return 0; it simply returns 0

step 8 : } it represents closing of main function definition part.